                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d696">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-02-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Leishman, replying to Mr. Hay’s telegram of February 2, reports that he has
                    already taken up the matters specially referred to, together with other cases,
                    very actively with the Sublime Porte; that the minister for foreign affairs
                    fully recognizes the justice and reasonableness of the demands and also the fact
                    that the United States Government had waited long enough for patience to cease
                    to be a virtue, and promised an answer not later than the end of the current
                    week.</p>
                <p>Mr. Leishman inquires if, under the circumstances named, he shall make an
                    immediate demand for audience with the Sultan, or if he shall wait until the
                    first of the coming week.)</p>
            </div>
